Program: Discovery
Title: Ancient Olympics - sport and politics
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jryrd
Last Broadcast Date: 10 August 2004
Fourth in a series of programmes on the ancient Olympic games. Why sport and politics could be a potent mixture. The programme explores how an athlete's sporting victory was also a political victory for the city he came from and victorious athletes were regarded as national heroes.